scripts.comment: BJC CS10 Project 2: Wordle™ Your job is to fill in the eight blocks below; when they are all correct, the game should play exactly as described in the specification.

custom-block.s: Play Worldle™ with secret word (if blank we choose for you) %txt and must all guesses be words? %b

custom-block.comment: Reports A given 1, B given 2, ... and Z given 26
Reports 1 given A, 2 given B, ..., and 26 given Z
Reports all the letters of its input (assumed to be a-zA-Z) in uppercase

Reports the number of occurrences of the letter in the word. You MUST use at least one higher-order function (HOF) in this block. You MAY NOT use any loops in this block (e.g., repeat, repeat until, for, or for each).

custom-block.s: game over? guess: %txt secret: %txt guess num: %n
custom-block.comment: Reports true if the guess equals the secret or if the number of guesses is six, and false otherwise.

custom-block.s: matching 123 slots between guess: %txt and secret: %txt
custom-block.comment: Reports a word of 1, 2, or 3 to indicate the “scoring” of all the letters of guess (in terms of their match with secret). Every “in-place” letter is a 3, any letter not in secret at all is a 1, and any letter not “in-place” but “out-of-place” is indicated by a 2. For a given letter, if there are more out-of-place letters in guess than secret, the 2s are assigned left-to-right until the number matches the number in secret, and the rest are assigned 1. You may assume the guess and secret have the same length.

This takes in a list of guesses and a secret and reports a “keyboard” -- a 26-digit-long (one for each letter A-Z) number made up of only the digits 0, 1, 2, or 3. The leftmost digit represents the letter “A”, the second-to-the-left digit represents the letter “B”, and so on. A digit of 0 means the letter was never guessed. A digit of 1 means that letter WAS guessed by (at least) one of the guesses, but was NOT in the secret at all. A digit of 2 means the letter was guessed by (at least) one of the guesses, was NEVER “in-place”, but WAS “out-of-place”. A digit of 3 means the letter was guessed by one of the guesses, and WAS “in-place” at least once. You may assume all the guesses have the same length as the secret.
